"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-british-paris-great-britain-gabby-thomas-stade-de-france-b2594535.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Georgia Bell confessed her \\\"unconventional route\\\" to the Olympic podium once seemed like a \\\"bonkers\\\" impossibility after collecting 1500 metres bronze at the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 520, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs_football\", \"score\": 0.7493733489858817, \"rank\": 0.3271907492639581, \"text\": \"Georgia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgia_Bulldogs_football\"}, {\"begin\": 504, \"end\": 519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bell's was one of threeBritishbronzes secured on Saturday night, the first beforeTeam GBadded a pair from the men's and women's 4x400m to make it a perfect five medals from as many relay finals inParis.\", \"from\": 522, \"to\": 724, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A medal on her Olympic debut was a remarkable achievement for 30-year-old Bell, once a prodigious youth talent who initially only took up running again to keep herself occupied during the Covid-19 lockdown.\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 932, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bell, who in a fairy-tale twist was also born in Paris, said: \\\"I have had so many nice messages from people, be them athletes or just parents or whatever saying, 'You have inspired me to get back into an old sport or an old hobby'.\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 1165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 983, \"end\": 988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5974744748500497e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When I got back into it, the goal wasn't to make the Olympics, that would have seemed kind of bonkers at the time.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1282, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But just keep going.\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's never too late to go back to something that you enjoy.\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1365, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am a happy athlete and I think anyone can take away from that, there is no set path.\", \"from\": 1366, \"to\": 1452, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mine's a very unconventional route.\\\"\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenya's Faith Kipyegon lowered the Olympic record to 3:51.29 to claim gold and defend her title for a second time, while Australia's Jessica Hull took silver, 0.05 seconds faster than Bell's new British record of 3:52.61.\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9991753168718427, \"rank\": 0.0008253283045767413, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 1499, \"end\": 1513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Faith Kipyegon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\"}, {\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9970393185643254, \"rank\": 0.0023147540768487162, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1624, \"end\": 1636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessica Hull\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\"}, {\"begin\": 1686, \"end\": 1700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Progression_of_the_British_football_transfer_fee_record\", \"score\": 0.9999999995811777, \"rank\": 4.1865964678702264e-10, \"text\": \"British record\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Progression_of_the_British_football_transfer_fee_record\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Progression_of_the_British_football_transfer_fee_record\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bell had clawed her way up by the final lap, the last of a leading group of four on the back stretch led by Kipyegon.\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Scotland's Laura Muir, who finished fifth on Saturday night, closed in on the final bend andGreat Britainwere sitting fourth and fifth going into the last stretch.\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1833, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8984501388208677, \"rank\": 0.10953111440493388, \"text\": \"Scotland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1844, \"end\": 1854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Muir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Muir\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Muir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Muir\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though some had predicted Tokyo silver medallist Muir might land herself on another podium in Paris, it was Bell who surged forward in the final 100 metres to beat Ethiopia's Diribe Welteji to bronze.\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2024, \"end\": 2029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999556369039035, \"rank\": 4.435660946153288e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2092, \"end\": 2097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5974744748500497e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2162, \"end\": 2170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999840838, \"rank\": 1.5967214488456826e-11, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 2173, \"end\": 2187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diribe_Welteji\", \"score\": 0.9999999998694875, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Diribe Welteji\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diribe_Welteji\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diribe_Welteji\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said: \\\"I only thought this week in the heats I could medal.\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I started to believe that this week.\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2300, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I know that training has been going really well.\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2351, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I know that I will never really be in this position again, where I can come into the Games with absolutely no pride.\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2472, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even making it to the Olympics was huge.\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So next year will be different.\", \"from\": 2515, \"to\": 2547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I will be an Olympic medallist and people will be expecting things.\\\"\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2616, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mine's a very unconventional route  Bell showed plenty of promise as a youngster, but a series of injuries and setbacks led to her completely stepping back from the track around 2017, when she was a student at the University of California.\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When Muir\\u00a0stormed to silver at the Tokyo 2020 Games, Bell, only just beginning to re-lace her trainers, was watching her future GB team-mate on television.\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 3014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She started with a few parkruns and was pleasantly surprised she still had the speed, so she rang up old coach Trevor Painter, who alongside Jenny Meadows also trains newly-crowned 800m champion Keely Hodgkinson, and started taking the sport seriously again.\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3157, \"end\": 3170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Meadows\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jenny Meadows\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Meadows\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Meadows\"}, {\"begin\": 3211, \"end\": 3227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As recently as May, Bell was still working a nine-to-five job in cybersecurity sales and a month later was crowned 1500m champion at the British Olympic trials to book her place in Paris.\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3413, \"end\": 3420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9910061376364738, \"rank\": 0.007898681663696193, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 3457, \"end\": 3462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5974744748500497e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said: \\\"Work said to me, 'If you go to the Olympics and got a medal we still want you back and, when they said that when I left on May 1, I thought there is no way I will win a medal.\", \"from\": 3465, \"to\": 3651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I will see, but probably have a chat with them.\", \"from\": 3652, \"to\": 3702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Things have changed.\\\"\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3724, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shortly after Bell kicked off the medal rush, the British quartet of Alex Haydock-Wilson, Matthew Hudson-Smith, Lewis Davey and Charlie Dobson added to the tally in a men's 4\\u00d7400 metres relay won by the United States in Olympic record time.\", \"from\": 3726, \"to\": 3966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3776, \"end\": 3783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9910061376364738, \"rank\": 0.007898681663696193, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 3795, \"end\": 3799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.8062512611321698, \"rank\": 0.23995056395791234, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}, {\"begin\": 3816, \"end\": 3836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Hudson-Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 3838, \"end\": 3843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\", \"score\": 0.995653197665395, \"rank\": 0.004365779510473961, \"text\": \"Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lewis_gun\"}, {\"begin\": 3844, \"end\": 3849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davey_Allison\", \"score\": 0.9999998969060524, \"rank\": 1.0309397115353986e-07, \"text\": \"Davey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davey_Allison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davey_Allison\"}, {\"begin\": 3862, \"end\": 3868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"score\": 0.9999997566910975, \"rank\": 1.3763363820324284e-07, \"text\": \"Dobson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2566598\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\"}, {\"begin\": 3929, \"end\": 3942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9203980769667326, \"rank\": 0.06702906737300271, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Haydock-Wilson led off for GB, and individual men's 400 metres silver medallist Hudson-Smith briefly had the Britons in front with a 43.09 second-leg split.\", \"from\": 3968, \"to\": 4124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3995, \"end\": 3997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9997871810128621, \"rank\": 0.00021286428861047447, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 4077, \"end\": 4084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9822976638144553, \"rank\": 0.011588124442849894, \"text\": \"Britons\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That advantage was quickly relinquished, and by the time Davey had handed over to Dobson both the US and Botswana had pulled well clear.\", \"from\": 4126, \"to\": 4262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4208, \"end\": 4214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"score\": 0.9999997566910975, \"rank\": 1.3763363820324284e-07, \"text\": \"Dobson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2566598\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\"}, {\"begin\": 4224, \"end\": 4226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9895162856897475, \"rank\": 0.01058372483008725, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4231, \"end\": 4239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999990207825495, \"rank\": 9.789519311163746e-07, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latter secured silver after individual 200 metres champion Letsile Tebogo blitzed to the finish in 43.04 seconds, the only man with a quicker split than Hudson-Smith.\", \"from\": 4264, \"to\": 4434, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dobson had considerable distance when he crossed the finish for a cumulative 2:55:83 to break a European record that had stood for 28 years and record the sixth-fastest time in history.\", \"from\": 4436, \"to\": 4621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4436, \"end\": 4442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"score\": 0.9999997566910975, \"rank\": 1.3763363820324284e-07, \"text\": \"Dobson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2566598\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Dobson\"}, {\"begin\": 4532, \"end\": 4547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9335465826828246e-20, \"text\": \"European record\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hudson-Smith said: \\\"I was literally on the floor after that.\", \"from\": 4623, \"to\": 4683, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I could not walk around the track.\", \"from\": 4684, \"to\": 4718, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But honestly, we say we are gonna fight for each other, and that's exactly what we did.\", \"from\": 4719, \"to\": 4806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We fought for each other.\", \"from\": 4808, \"to\": 4834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We came over the line in the national record and could not ask for anything.\", \"from\": 4835, \"to\": 4911, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We put our heart and soul into that run, and it's an amazing, amazing feeling just to come away with a team medal and deliver for our country and also for ourselves and PB.\\\"\", \"from\": 4912, \"to\": 5085, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5081, \"end\": 5083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\", \"score\": 0.9999999998526619, \"rank\": 1.4714869434108817e-10, \"text\": \"PB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Victoria Ohuruogu, Amber Anning, Laviai Nielsen and Nicole Yeargin secured bronze of their own 15 minutes later, ensuring Great Britain would take home a medal from all\\u00a0 five relays in Paris.\", \"from\": 5087, \"to\": 5278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5087, \"end\": 5104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_Ohuruogu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victoria Ohuruogu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_Ohuruogu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victoria_Ohuruogu\"}, {\"begin\": 5120, \"end\": 5134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laviai_Nielsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laviai Nielsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laviai_Nielsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laviai_Nielsen\"}, {\"begin\": 5139, \"end\": 5153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Yeargin\", \"score\": 0.9999959818036371, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicole Yeargin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Yeargin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Yeargin\"}, {\"begin\": 5209, \"end\": 5222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999995571589423, \"rank\": 4.4280558009790074e-07, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 5272, \"end\": 5277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5974744748500497e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Champions the United States employed Paris 200 metres championGabby Thomasand Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone, who on Thursday night lowered her own world record to 50.37 seconds in the 400 metres hurdles.\", \"from\": 5280, \"to\": 5479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5294, \"end\": 5307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9203980769667326, \"rank\": 0.06702906737300271, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5317, \"end\": 5322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5974744748500497e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5358, \"end\": 5364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.7832199535241031, \"rank\": 0.27676974167160806, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans dominated in 3:15.27 but it was a much closer battle for the remaining places on the podium.\", \"from\": 5481, \"to\": 5587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5481, \"end\": 5494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.309956706960112e-21, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All five top teams secured national or area records, with the British quartet lowering theirs to 3:19.72.\", \"from\": 5589, \"to\": 5694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5651, \"end\": 5658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9910061376364738, \"rank\": 0.007898681663696193, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Individual 400 metres finalist Anning said: \\\"At this point it was all mental.\", \"from\": 5696, \"to\": 5773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was more about the team.\", \"from\": 5774, \"to\": 5803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did my part, I knew we had a great opportunity to get a medal so this is for the girls.\", \"from\": 5804, \"to\": 5893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just wanted to get it round and it was close at the end but I just had a little bit of a surge and brought it home.\", \"from\": 5894, \"to\": 6011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's been an amazing Games, we have had great support, big thanks to Team GB and I am just glad all the relay teams could come home with medals.\\\"\", \"from\": 6013, \"to\": 6159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6083, \"end\": 6090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 6.888523244662867e-12, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamaica looked to be in contention, but ruled themselves out in the second leg when Andrenette Knight lost the baton after bumping into Ireland's Rhasidat Adeleke.\", \"from\": 6161, \"to\": 6324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6161, \"end\": 6168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999999822649, \"rank\": 1.7644739605559306e-11, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 6297, \"end\": 6304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.5340939188589159, \"rank\": 0.4680577564900181, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 6307, \"end\": 6323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhasidat_Adeleke\", \"score\": 0.9999999999349711, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rhasidat Adeleke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhasidat_Adeleke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhasidat_Adeleke\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anchor Anning pulled Great Britain into second on the back straight but, as she approached the finish, found herself in a neck-and-neck battle with the Netherlands and Ireland.\", \"from\": 6326, \"to\": 6502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6347, \"end\": 6360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999995571589423, \"rank\": 4.4280558009790074e-07, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"ht